(thirdQuint)Influence of Coffee on the Health and on the Heart of Normal, Diabetics e Coronary Artery Disease Patients.

 Patients will have a wash-out period (21 days) with no coffee or other caffeine-drinks.

 Then they will be submitted to treadmill test, MAPA, Holter-ECG and vascular reactivity study, biochemical and inflammatory plasma dosages, as basal.

 Then they will start a period of coffee drinking over 4 weeks; and all exams will be repeated.

 We will study two types of coffee, arabica and robusta; with two types of toasted beans(regular and soft).

 Also regular and decaffeinated coffee.

 A total of 300 (100 normal people, 100 diabetics, 100 coronary disease) individuals will be tested.

